<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Meadville, PA 5/18/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.80)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=400'>R. "Voice of Law" Smith</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=400&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 20, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Six-game Swiss tourney for a Sting sword at Fantasy Cards & Comics in Meadville, PA. Director Chris LoBue. 18 participants.<br />
<br />
PRE-TOURNEY<br />
Rewind to mid-April: I&#8217;m perusing the LOTR tourney listings for May trying to decide which ONE tournament I can make it to. Having a life does not cooperate too well with playing cards on Saturdays.<br />
Two tournaments catch my interest: PA territorials and this tournament for a Sting sword. I decide against PA territorials for the following reasons:<br />
1. They are in York, PA. I&#8217;d rather drive up the interstate for a shot at a tangible prize than trek across Amish country for a shot at a pat on the hiney from Decipher.<br />
2. The entry fee for states is like 17 bucks&#8230;the entry fee for the Sting tournament is only five. Factor in gas and tolls and I&#8217;m looking at a significant investment driving to York.<br />
3. The man in charge of states apparently cannot spell the word &#8220;territorial.&#8221;<br />
So Sting tourney it is, and I begin playtesting decks.<br />
<br />
Fast-forward to the day of the tournament: I wake up after a decent 7 hours, triple-check my deck (look for the list coming soon), pack my caads and hit the road. Stop at the donut shop for breakfast and am served by the only fine-looking female I will meet all day. Apparently Meadville was devoid of do-able ladies, much to my chagrin. About 5 miles outside of Meadville, I fly by a PA state trooper on I-79 going 80 miles an hour. I slam on the brakes but still only slow to 72, but the guy does NOT pull me over and I am home free. Find the shop with ease, Mapquest worked for once. Play a fun game with my Dwarf/Moria deck and win. The tourney starts up&#8230;<br />
<br />
REAL GAME INFO BEGINS HERE<br />
Game 1 vs. Jeremy Hoople<br />
The guy I played in my fun game. He&#8217;s using a different deck though so I&#8217;m not totally sure what to expect.<br />
I win the bid and let him go first as I usually do. I&#8217;m playing Uruks and they slow him down of course. His Shadow side is just a bunch of low-cost Moria minions, in fact it seems like 95% of his Shadow side was minions. He got out a They Are Coming in the middle of the game but I shot it down quickly with a Secret Sentinels.<br />
I get Sting out at site 3 and use it every turn from then on, and every turn I see 5 or 6 Orcs in his hand (which essentially lets me play things without worrying about the Pool). Every turn, he plays them, and every turn, they die to archery and skirmishes. At first I was worried that he might be able to stack a bunch of guys on Frodo and take him out that way, but I realized soon enough that even though he was playing 5 or 6 guys a site, they were all easily disposed of.<br />
I play it safe and move one site at a time, and he is doing the same because my Uruks are really tearing into him. I know I can double-move on him whenever I need to, but I never end up needing to because he succumbs to the Uruk smash at about site 7. Uneventful FW. +3, total 3<br />
<br />
Good: easy first game wins are how I like to start off my tourneys. Also Jeremy was a great opponent in both of our games, thanks man.<br />
Bad: *Yawn*<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 2 vs. Daniel Fischer<br />
Bleh I can&#8217;t remember this game. Even if I could it wouldn&#8217;t do anyone any good to read about it. Basically it was me smashing some poor kid into the ground. He was alright about it all, though, we had a few laughs and went our separate ways. FW. +3, total 6<br />
<br />
Good: Win.<br />
Bad: Business as usual. I&#8217;m getting too old for this.<br />
<br />
Game 3 vs. Luke Mitchell<br />
Before the tourney I was talking to this kid and his mom, explaining how long the tourney would be, how it was Swiss style so you don&#8217;t get eliminated, etc. They were both pretty cool. So I sit down with this kid and I&#8217;m like &#8220;what site do you want me to kill you at?&#8221; Talkin trash and stuff. And he&#8217;s like &#8220;no site&#8221; and I say &#8220;that&#8217;s not an answer to my question&#8221; and so he says &#8220;site 9.&#8221; So I&#8217;m like ok, site 9 it is.<br />
Anyway I don&#8217;t draw any minions this game. I win the bid and let him go first but I wouldn&#8217;t have if I would&#8217;ve known that alls I would draw is Free Peoples cards. His site 1 is that one that says exert a guy to play a guy &#8211;1, except he thinks he can play a guy &#8211;1 FROM DECK and I&#8217;m like, no man. He uses my site 3 Waterfall to move 1-4 first turn, and all I have for him is a Uruk Captain. I use my site 3 also and tie him at site 6, but he&#8217;s ahead and moves 6-8, only seeing a Troop. I draw my Gift of Boats and all 3 Secret Sentinels but NO ELVEN ALLIES. I move to site 7 and stop because I finally have some minions and I&#8217;m going to try my best to make good on my promise and kill him at site 9.<br />
He moves into site 9 with Aragorn the King, Bozomir the Lord, and Frodo with a sword. I&#8217;ve got a Captain, a Warrior, a Scout, Lurtz, and Lurtz&#8217;s Sword in hand, and a Troop in the lost pile. I get 14 pool because he played Orophin that turn, and he&#8217;s moving into my Slopes. I can either: play Lurtz and a couple other guys; or play the Captain, use him to pull a 3-cost Uruk, and play a total of 5 guys. That&#8217;s what I opt to do, but it really didn&#8217;t matter WHAT I did because the kid had a friggin Elendil&#8217;s Valor in hand to make Bozo defender +1, and like I said he had just played Orophin, so one of my guys gets gunned down. It really wasn&#8217;t pretty. Gornie and Bozo both die, but Frodo makes it easily. Bad draw gets me a FL, +1 total 7<br />
<br />
Good: Lucky kid<br />
Bad: hate to discount an opponent&#8217;s victory, but I got the SHAFT<br />
<br />
So now I&#8217;m seriously worried about my chances of winning this thing. I go across the street to the convenience store for a roast beef sub and am served by a real friendly older lady, but no chicks in sight. Come back in time for &#8230;<br />
<br />
Game 4 vs. Elliott Randall<br />
He&#8217;s playing some half-assed Moria shadow with a really focus-less FP side. I could tell his deck was limited by his collection. He starts off with Legolas the Prince and the new Gimli. At this point in the tournament everyone is smelling the blood in the water of me losing a game, and I have lost some of the air of invulnerability that usually surrounds me at these things. So this kid wants to beat me too.<br />
But that aint happening today. I win the bid and let him go. He starts some random sucko site, and admits to me that this is the first time he has ever played his site 1. OK...<br />
He plays a bunch of guys first turn then moves to Ettenmoors, I&#8217;m like SAVAGERY and two guys die. He plays a bunch more companions but nothing to boost them so the Uruks take em out. By the time he gets to site 6, everyone is dead except Frodo, he wants to play two Lorien Elves but I say &#8220;can you spot an Elf?&#8221; and he says &#8220;no&#8221; and moves to site 7 and loses. Yawn. FW +3 total 10<br />
<br />
Good: I actually drew some minions<br />
Bad: kid<br />
<br />
Game 5 vs Adam Mumford<br />
Holy shiot, this guy is my age. So we have a game finally.<br />
I win the bid and let him go first. He starts Gandalf I think, and drops Bozo the LoG first turn. Faces some resistance going through Ettenmoors, but doubles into my Waterfall nonetheless. I deal some significant wounds but don&#8217;t take anyone out. At this time some other dude is sitting at the table BS&#8217;ing to him and it&#8217;s really getting on my nerves but I&#8217;m being civil about it.<br />
I take my first turn, drop Celeborn and Aragorn and move. He gets twelve pool and lo and behold he is playing Nazgul. So I&#8217;m thinking crap, I have Aragorn, Arwen, and Lego all naked against a Nazgul deck at Ettenmoors, I could be in trouble. But all he drops is Attea and I just put Gornie on him both times. Then I&#8217;m wondering if I can double move when I remember I have ARV in hand, so I move on and he drops another Nazgul, with a Sword I think. So I play the ARV in maneuver, and the jackoff who was sitting there says, and I am not making this up: &#8220;Isn&#8217;t that a regroup action?&#8221; I&#8217;m already pissed at this goon for being generally loud and obnoxious, so I just look at him with a face that could melt the ears off a gundark and throw the card in his general direction. My opponent glances at it and says &#8220;ok,&#8221; then I say &#8220;ok, then I&#8217;ll shoot your two guys down with Lego.&#8221; And my opponent is like &#8220;Wha? I thought it only exhausted one guy&#8221; and I&#8217;m like don&#8217;t you realize that ARV is the best FP card in the game??? Apparently not. I explain it all and the Nazgul go away. GAH<br />
So I get a Troop and a Warrior out at Hollin and stop him there. The annoying guy finally gets up and leaves. I get Arwen on her horse and also find a Gwemegil, so the move to Hollin is easy. I have to explain how Arwen is power FIFTEEN, but after that all is good. I stay at site 4 anyway because I&#8217;m not ready to move past him yet.<br />
My Uruks stop him at site 5 again, and I&#8217;m right behind him. I play Bozo the Log at site 4, and when he pulls a Balrog on me I just stick two wounds on Gornie and two on Bozo. I decide to go ahead and double ahead of him to site 6, and between my allies and the fact that Lego and Arwen are both still fresh I slide in scott-free.<br />
He goes and has to stop at the sanctuary to heal. I reconcile and draw my Flaming Brand. I already had a Ranger&#8217;s Sword and a Last Alliance so the Brand makes Gornie power 16 damage +2&#8230;Plus I&#8217;m in the lead&#8230;I think you can figure out how this game ended.<br />
FW +3 total 13<br />
<br />
Good: Semi-competitive game for once<br />
Bad: the regroup action guy, having to explain ARV and Asfaloth and even Flaming Brand&#8230;bleh whatever<br />
<br />
So now I get to play the only undefeated player remaining&#8230;.<br />
<br />
Game 6 vs Jason Hawthorne<br />
I know Jason from league nights and other tourneys, he&#8217;s a great player and an even better opponent. I&#8217;m looking forward to our game, but I really don&#8217;t wanna lose and go 4-2 (yuck). He has had a chance to check out parts of some of my games so he knows what I&#8217;m playing, but I seriously have no idea what he is playing. I come to find out it&#8217;s a deck a lot like mine, only with more of a Gandalf focus.<br />
I win the bid 2-1 and against my usual strategy I choose to go first. I play the Pony and pull Gornie, I got 6 shadow cards opening hand so I just move. He&#8217;s playing Ettenmoors too but only has a Troop for me. I take two on Gornie and move on. He doesn&#8217;t have anything at site 3 Arwen takes a couple hits and we reconcile. He goes and plays a bunch of crap and puts way too much in the pool, so I let him have it with all the shadow cards I drew opening hand. He has to stop at Ettenmoors.<br />
From then on, we each move one site a time, a Uruk slugfest at every turn. I&#8217;m 2 sites ahead though, and I have Sting to check what pumpers he has each turn and whether I can double-move or not. I move into site 9 (he&#8217;s playing the Slopes also) and survive with very little fanfare. FW +3 total 16<br />
<br />
So now there are no undefeateds, and with the whole tie-breaker thing the top 4 looks like this:<br />
1. Reid Smith<br />
2. Jason Hawthorne<br />
3. Scott (?)<br />
4. Adam Mumford<br />
There is some discussion as to whether there will be a playoff or not, and they decide to have one. Bleh, unsanctioned games. So I get paired against Scott in the first game:<br />
<br />
Game 7 vs. Scott<br />
I also know Scott from league/locals, he and Jason tend to carpool to tourneys often. He also has had a chance to check out a game or two of mine, while I have no clue what he is playing. I win the bid here and again opt to go first. I play a bunch of stuff first turn, including Sting. Sting him and see a bunch of Sauron stuff and a Troop of Uruk-Hai (?). I remove a bunch of pool and walk into his site 2, Weathertop. He plays the Troop and I put two wounds on Gornie, then move to his Council Courtyard. Ask him why he&#8217;s playing Weathertop and he says &#8220;it&#8217;s a decoy&#8221; and also says he likes the high shadow number. Hmm. He plays a Red-Eye scrub minion and I take some more wounds from the Troop, bleh. No more than 5 wounds so the sanctuary will cover it next turn.<br />
He goes and pulls Gornie, also plays another companion (I don&#8217;t remember who), which puts him up to the magic number 5. He moves and I drop some Uruks and play Savagery x2 (!) and two companions die. He stops.<br />
That pretty much sums up the game there, I Sting every turn which removes massive amounts of pool because he has a handful of Red-Eye orcs that he cant play because they&#8217;re roaming and I&#8217;m taking all his pool with Sting! A vicious cycle. Meantime his fellowship is suffering because he is unable to supply them with boosters of any sort. I overwhelm Frodo at site 5 I think. FW.<br />
<br />
Jason wins over Adam so it would be him and me in the final. I&#8217;m hoping that, since A. I beat Jason in the tourney and B. I won against all 3 of the guys in the final, we won&#8217;t even have to play this game, and I&#8217;ll just take the win. But no such luck&#8230;<br />
<br />
FINAL<br />
Vs Jason Hawthorne<br />
This game, we each bid 2, he wins the die roll and lets me go first. We each move one site at a time, not out of restraint, but out of necessity as we are each getting good minion hands and dropping serious Uruk beats on each other. He is slowly building an unstoppable fellowship though. He gets Bozomir out with an Armor (which works for two sites before I draw a Beyond The Height of Men). G-Man has his Staff to cancel skirmys, and J even plays a Wielder of the Flame at one site to stack two big Uruks on Gandalf. What really impresses me, though, is he gets Frodo stocked with Sting, O Elbereth!, and Mithril Coat, and a Bounder on the side. Plus he is playing Old Bilbo&#8217;s Hair so the Bounder heals every turn. This means that Frodo can withstand up to power 20, and all he takes is ONE wound. The only thing that stops J from double moving past me is the fact that all these toys cost him serious pool, which I translate into Uruk smashing. So we end up tied at site 6 and it&#8217;s my turn. I Sting and see Troop, Captain, Bred For Battle, Savagery x2, and Battle Cry. I move to the no archery site with Gornie, Arwen, and Lego. I got ARV x2 in my hand, and I play one there so none of his guys can use the Bred For Battle. I use Gwemegil to bait out the two Savageries, and J uses the Battle Cry to put Arwen away. I stop and he goes. Moves into the no arch site and I have enough baddies to stop him. I reconcile and draw PATHS x2. HUGE. I sting and see a Tower Assassin (which had been in his hand all game long), a Lurtz, an Organic Assassin, and a bunch of FP cards. I move to his site 8 (the Shores) and he gets 12 pool. Drops the O. Assassin and Lurtz, emptying the pool. I play my other ARV and mow down the two Uruks with Lego. I still have my two PATHS so I decide to move, and he reconciles and gets nothing. That&#8217;s the game&#8230;<br />
<br />
Good: a closer game than my first with J, tho both our games were really good<br />
Bad: that one of us had to lose<br />
<br />
So I win the tourney and the Sting sword, yay. I hit the road and still have time to make it to a party that night (glad I didn&#8217;t drive to York).<br />
<br />
Proops:<br />
The director<br />
The venue<br />
The prize<br />
Jason for being the luckiest sob ever and getting a foil rare one ring in the mail for winning a previous tourney<br />
The cop for NOT pulling me over<br />
<br />
Sloops:<br />
States for being so friggin far away, not even in a major city. I mean, when you think Pennsylvania, you think PITTSBURGH, or Philly, or maybe Erie or Harrisburg or Hershey. But honestly, for those who read this who do not live near PA, did you even know that York, PA exists??<br />
Bad draws that make you lose games to kids<br />
Meadville for having no chicks<br />
Drew Ferguson for dragging me into this lousy game and then abandoning it, and for not accepting my invitation to accompany me to this tourney<br />
Jim Li, just for being himself<br />
<br />
That&#8217;s all, and check out my deck, The Gaffi Stick, coming soon!<br />
